<h1>Bibliography of Published Sources relating to University History</h1>

<p>Published sources are often useful background reading before 'plunging' into in-depth, archives-based research.  The following list is not exhaustive but is being added to as we identify useful texts to direct people towards.</p>
<p>Some have begun to appear online at the <a href="http://www.archive.org/" target="_blank">Internet Archive</a> and links are provided to these. Others can be consulted here and links are given to the main Library Catalogue.</p>

<h2>Institutional Histories</h2>

<ul style="padding-bottom:10px">
<li><strong>History of the University of Edinburgh, from 1580 to 1646 : to which is prefixed the charter granted to the college by James VI of Scotland, in 1582</strong> (<a href="http://archive.org/details/historyuniversi00craugoog" target="_blank"">View</a>) - Thomas Craufurd (1808)</li>
<li><strong>The History of the University of Edinburgh: Chiefly Compiled from Original Papers and Records ... </strong> (<a href="http://archive.org/details/historyuniversi02bowegoog" target="_blank">View</a>) - Alexander Bower (1830)</li>
<li><strong>History of the University of Edinburgh from its foundation</strong> (<a href="http://archive.org/details/historyofunivers01dalzuoft" target="_blank">Volume 1</a> :: <a href="http://archive.org/details/historyofunivers02dalzuoft" target="_blank">Volume 2</a>) - Andrew Dalzel (1862)</li>
<li><strong>The story of the University of Edinburgh during its first three hundred years</strong> (<a href="http://archive.org/details/storyuniversity07grangoog" target="_blank">Volume 1</a> :: <a href="http://archive.org/details/storyuniversity06grangoog" target="_blank">Volume 2</a>) - Sir Alexander Grant<br />
<em>covers the period 1583-1883</em></li>
<li><strong>Edinburgh University, A Sketch of its Life for 300 Years</strong> (<a href="http://archive.org/details/edinburghuniver00univgoog" target="_blank">View</a>) (1884)</li>
<li><strong>University of Edinburgh : Charters, statutes, and acts of the Town council and the Senatus, 1583-1858</strong> (1937) (not available online - <a href="http://catalogue.lib.ed.ac.uk/vwebv/holdingsInfo?bibId=26218" target="_blank">local copies</a>)</li>
<li><strong>History of the University of Edinburgh, 1883-1933</strong> - Sir Arthur Logan Turner (not available online - <a href="http://catalogue.lib.ed.ac.uk/vwebv/holdingsInfo?bibId=91290" target="_blank">local copies</a>)</li>
<li><strong>A Short History of the University of Edinburgh, 1556-1889</strong> - David Bayne Horne (1967) (not available online - <a href="http://catalogue.lib.ed.ac.uk/vwebv/holdingsInfo?bibId=6734" target="_blank">local copies</a>)</li>
<li><strong>Four Centuries: Edinburgh University Life, 1583-1983</strong> - Gordon Donaldson, Ed. (1983) (not available online - <a href="http://catalogue.lib.ed.ac.uk/vwebv/holdingsInfo?bibId=28680" target="_blank">local copies</a>)</li>
<li><strong>The University of Edinburgh : an illustrated history</strong> - Anderson, Lynch &amp; Phillipson (2003) (not available online - <a href="http://catalogue.lib.ed.ac.uk/vwebv/holdingsInfo?bibId=1217082" target="_blank">local copies</a>)</li>
</ul>

